# GIGI Sheets — environment configuration. Copy to `.env.local` for
# local development, or set these in the Vercel dashboard for
# production. Vite inlines `VITE_*` vars at build time, so any change
# requires a rebuild / redeploy to take effect.

# ── Engine URL ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The GIGI engine HTTP base. Local dev defaults to http://localhost:3142
# when this is unset.
#
# Production MUST set this to an https:// URL. A non-HTTPS URL on a
# non-localhost host will REFUSE to start (`resolveEngineBaseUrl` in
# src/App.tsx) — better to fail loudly than ship a plaintext-HTTP
# data pipe. Example for davisgeometric.com:
#
#   VITE_GIGI_BASE_URL=https://api.davisgeometric.com
#
VITE_GIGI_BASE_URL=

# ── Auth origin ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Origin of the davisgeometric.com magic-link auth service. Sign-in is
# disabled when this is unset.
#
# Allowed values are hard-coded in `src/lib/use-account.ts`
# (ALLOWED_AUTH_ORIGINS) — adding a new origin requires a code change,
# preventing misconfiguration from exfiltrating the session cookie.
# Empty string ("") is an explicit opt-in to same-origin auth paths
# (useful when sheets is hosted at davisgeometric.com/gigi/sheets/ and
# the auth endpoints live on the same origin under /api/auth/...).
#
#   VITE_AUTH_BASE_URL=https://davisgeometric.com
# or, for same-origin deployment:
#   VITE_AUTH_BASE_URL=
#
VITE_AUTH_BASE_URL=
